PyCelonis Core - Python Http Client for Celonis EMS
==================================

[![License: Celonis Tools License Agreement](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-Celonis%20Tools%20License%20Agreement-brightgreen)](https://celonis.github.io/pycelonis/license.html)
[![Pycelonis Documentation](https://img.shields.io/badge/Docs-pycelonis-yellow)](https://celonis.github.io/pycelonis/index.html)

## Overview
PyCelonis Core provides following components:
- http client based on [httpx](https://github.com/encode/httpx/)
- base model to interact with Celonis resource objects

## Usage
PyCelonis Core can be used standalone to interact with Celonis EMS API.
1. configure the client:

```py
from pycelonis_core.client.client import Client

client = Client(
    base_url=<celonis-url>,
    api_token=<api_token>,
    key_type=KEY_TYPE.<KEY_TYPE>,
    **kwargs
)
```
2. Interact with EMS:
```py
# get a list of pools
client.request(method="GET", url="/integration/api/pools")
```

## Troubleshooting
Need help? Read the [docs](https://celonis.github.io/pycelonis/index.html) or Contact Celonis support.
